Shimizu
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1161,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
- Ovipositor sheath of moderate length, less than 1.8 × as long as hind tibia; propodeum without submedial longitudinal carinae resulting in an open area superomedia; second hind tarsomere 2.0 × as long as wide [
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1102,1308,1330]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">China</collectingCountry>
]...... 
